definitions.definition: ( Egyptology ) The region in the sky in which the sun tarries just before it rises or after it sets .

main_definition: ( Egyptology ) The region in the sky in which the sun tarries just before it rises or after it sets .

definitions.definition: One of the three seasons of Ancient Egypt , coming after Shemu and before Peret ; Inundation .
